sports video all √ó from to you have successfully emailed the post √ó  key lessons from sheryl sandbergs favorite business book michael benninger blinkist may    pm  facebook linkedin twitter email print she knows a thing or two about sustaining a successful business emma mcintyre  stringer  getty images as chief operating officer of facebook sheryl sandberg knows a thing or two about sustaining a successful business like many other leading luminaries of the tech industry shes a voracious reader who credits the habit with helping her achieve such stratospheric heights the lean startup by eric ries is a favorite she recommends to all entrepreneurs written to help new ventures develop sustainable business models quickly this book advocates taking a scientific approach to building a business by continuously refining products based on feedback if youre interested in ensuring your startups success these seven insights from the lean startup can keep your business on the right track  focus the entire startup on a single goal as a startup your primary goal is to find a profitable and sustainable business model the faster you do that the more likely youll be to succeed start by focusing the entire company on finding out which products your potential customers want only after youve figured this out should you try to translate customers desire into dollars  use validated learning to find and test your business model your best bet for effectively selling the right product to the right people is by using a scientific approach known as validated learning begin by hypothesizing whether and how a certain product will be successful then find out if people will actually buy it by offering it to them and observing their reactions amazon  develop a minimal viable product to test your idea in the market in order to quickly find out whether demand for your idea truly exists create a minimal viable product mvp to collect meaningful feedback this barebones version of your concept should only contain the essential components but should be substantial enough to give potential customers a realistic product experience  build measure learn as fast as possible after creating a prototype of your product establish a buildmeasurelearn bml loop to continuously improve upon it gather authentic feedback on your prototype and based on what you learn conceptualize and construct an improved version rinse and repeat as rapidly as possible to find your optimal business model more quickly  use splittesting to optimize your idea to help you determine which of your products features customers find valuable ‚Äî and which they dont ‚Äî create two versions of your concept one with a new feature and one without it this type of splittesting makes it easy to see which version customers prefer helping you decide which features to keep ‚Äî and which to ditch  be prepared to pivot if your initial hypothesis isnt playing out as planned it might be time for a pivot this fundamental change of course might mean redefining your core values targeting a different customer segment or choosing a new sales channel making the decision to pivot isnt easy but many successful startups have done so and it shouldnt be avoided  concentrate on your current customers while it might be tempting for startups to pursue new customers at all costs a safer strategy is to get current customers to use your product increasingly often by regularly offering new features or providing new services your current advocates will become more vocal making it more likely your product will go viral more from blinkist see also facebook coo sheryl sandberg you can be the boss and still be terrified now watch study shows most of your facebook friends aren‚Äôt really your friends more blinkist sheryl sandberg business books facebook linkedin twitter email print √ó recommended for you powered by sailthru  key lessons from sheryl sandbergs favorite business book  key lessons from sheryl sandbergs favorite business book as chief operating officer of facebook sheryl recommended for you disclaimer featured apple is lagging the market as iphone  woes mount more the bottom line¬†¬ª heres how much you need to save for college every year depending on when you start more year by year¬†¬ª strategy emails  alerts get the best of business insider delivered to your inbox every day signup get the slide deck from henry blodgets ignition presentation on the future of digital ¬† ¬† read business insider on the go available on ios or android find a job tech jobs clevel jobs media jobs design jobs finance jobs sales jobs see all jobs ¬ª thanks to our partners follow us on also check out  copyright   business insider inc all rights reserved registration on or use of this site constitutes acceptance of our terms of service and privacy policy disclaimer commerce policy made in nyc stock quotes by finanzennet international editions ukdeausinmysgplsenlfritjp mark zuckerberg‚Äôs most valuable friend  the new york times nytimescom no longer supports internet explorer  or earlier please upgrade your browser learn more ¬ª sections home search skip to content skip to navigation view mobile version the new york times business daymark zuckerberg‚Äôs most valuable friend search subscribe now log in  settings close search advertisement supported by business day mark zuckerberg‚Äôs most valuable friend by miguel helftoct   continue reading the main story share this page continue reading the main story palo alto califevery monday a bit before  am sheryl sandberg facebook‚Äôs chief operating officer dashes off a quick email to her boss mark zuckerberg ‚Äúwe have a routine‚Äù ms sandberg says ‚Äúi email ‚Äòcoming in‚Äô he replies ‚Äòon my way‚Äô¬†‚Äùa few minutes later mr zuckerberg facebook‚Äôs cofounder and chief executive walks into the company‚Äôs headquarters here says a few hellos and heads to a conference room where he and ms sandberg huddle for an hour the two executives end the week the same way with a closeddoor meeting on friday afternoon they discuss products strategy deals personnel ‚Äî and each other‚Äúwe agreed that we would give each other feedback every friday‚Äù ms sandberg says ‚Äúwe are constantly flagging things nothing ever builds up‚Äù at a recent meeting for instance they ironed out a disagreement between them over the details of mr zuckerberg‚Äôs pledge to give  million to schools in newarkif all of that sounds a bit touchyfeely well it is ms sandberg a wellregarded internet executive is known for her interpersonal skills as much as for her sharp intellect and her regular meetings with the famously introverted mr zuckerberg have helped to keep one of silicon valley‚Äôs most unusual business partnerships working wonders for facebook advertisement continue reading the main story indeed for a variety of reasons ms sandberg may well have become mr zuckerberg‚Äôs most valuable friend continue reading the main story advertisement continue reading the main story since ms sandberg joined the company more than two years ago facebook has successfully navigated one of the more perilous stages in a startup‚Äôs life a period of hypergrowth facebook‚Äôs work force has expanded sixfold to nearly  and its global audience has multiplied by more than seven to half a billion revenue once little more than an afterthought is expected to balloon to around  billion this year according to estimates from wedbush securities facebook a private company doesn‚Äôt disclose its revenuepart of the reason for that sales growth is ms sandberg‚Äôs close ties to many of the world‚Äôs largest advertisers relationships she first developed as a senior executive at google ms sandberg also brought stability to facebook which had suffered from a long period of turmoil and the departure of several executives and early employees including the company‚Äôs other cofounders‚Äúone of the reasons the company is doing so well is because the two of them get along so well‚Äù says mike schroepfer vice president for engineeringms sandberg has focused on building the business expanding internationally cultivating relationships with large advertisers and putting her polish on things like communications and public policy that has freed mr zuckerberg to focus on what he likes best the facebook web site and its platformdonald graham the chairman of the washington post company who once tried to hire ms sandberg says that in the last two years a lot of questions about facebook‚Äôs viability have been put to rest‚Äúthe combination of mark and sheryl is the primary reason‚Äù says mr graham who is also a member of facebook‚Äôs boardthese days ms sandberg is also juggling another duty mounting a defense of mr zuckerberg at a time when a new movie ‚Äúthe social network‚Äù portrays him as an aloof and conniving student who may have stolen the idea for facebook from others ms sandberg will have none of that advertisement continue reading the main story ‚Äúhe is shy and introverted and he often does not seem very warm to people who don‚Äôt know him but he is warm‚Äù ms sandberg says of mr zuckerberg her voice rising with empathy ‚Äúhe really cares about the people who work here‚Äùshe can be just as protective of mr zuckerberg in privateat a technology conference this summer for instance mr zuckerberg flopped during an onstage interview he gave rambling answers to questions about facebook‚Äôs privacy policies became visibly nervous and started sweating profusely after the interview ms sandberg encouraged him not to beat himself up over it but to focus on parts of the interview that went well so he could do better next time according to people briefed on their interaction who didn‚Äôt want to be identified because they were not authorized to discuss the matter photo sheryl sandberg is credited with helping to guide the growth of facebook ‚Äî and her boss credit todd heislerthe new york times ‚Äúshe really wants him to succeed‚Äù says one of these peoplefor all her achievements there‚Äôs one area where ms sandberg‚Äôs influence has yet to work its magic privacy concerns while ms sandberg is not ultimately responsible for the features on the facebook site ‚Äî that‚Äôs mr zuckerberg‚Äôs job ‚Äî she is deeply involved in the planning that revolves around them she readily acknowledges that facebook has made mistakes‚Äúit is completely fair to say that we have had our challenges around privacy‚Äù she saysms sandberg says that facebook built powerful privacy controls but that they became too complicated for the average user facebook recently simplified those settings ‚Äúmark took the step to apologize‚Äù about the privacy problems she notesbut some critics say the privacy issue goes beyond how easily users understand facebook‚Äôs settings for example they note facebook collects increasing amounts of personal information from users to help marketers finetune their messages‚Äúi fear that ms sandberg is failing to provide the adult supervision that facebook requires‚Äù says jeff chester executive director of the center for digital democracy an advocacy group based in washington ‚Äúfacebook‚Äôs direction regarding its use of its member data and the viral and largely stealth marketing practices it endorses is very disturbing‚Äùa spokesman for facebook said the site lets users control what information they want to share and with whom and makes it clear how the information may be used in its advertising products facebook never sells that information to third parties the spokesman saidmark zuckerberg and sheryl sandberg may well be silicon valley‚Äôs oddest couplemr zuckerberg a yearold engineer and product visionary is socially awkward and reserved at  ms sandberg is the opposite polished personable chatty and at ease in the limelight advertisement continue reading the main story the differences don‚Äôt end there mr zuckerberg dropped out of harvard after his sophomore year to focus on building facebook and has never worked anywhere else ms sandberg who has a harvard mba is a veteran of google where she had a central role in building the largest most successful advertising business on the internetby the time she left google her unit had grown from a handful of people to about  employees or about onequarter of google‚Äôs total and it accounted for more than half of the company‚Äôs revenue she also helped to establish google‚Äôs philanthropic arm and ran operations for a collection of unrelated projects like google‚Äôs bookscanning operationseric schmidt google‚Äôs chief executive says he considers ms sandberg to be a ‚Äúsuperstar‚Äù but there is growing tension between the two companies in part because ms sandberg has recruited a string of former google executives and employees about  exgooglers are now working at facebook newsletter sign up continue reading the main story please verify youre not a robot by clicking the box invalid email address please reenter you must select a newsletter to subscribe to sign up you agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for the new york timess products and services thank you for subscribing an error has occurred please try again later you are already subscribed to this email view all new york times newsletters see sample manage email preferences not you privacy policy opt out or contact us anytime before coming to silicon valley in  ms sandberg earned a degree in economics and then her mba from harvard did stints at the world bank and at mckinsey  company and then worked as chief of staff for lawrence h summers when he was treasury secretary in the clinton administrationdespite their obvious differences ‚Äî or maybe because of them ‚Äî mr zuckerberg and ms sandberg have grown close ‚Äúa lot of people choose to hire people who look exactly like them‚Äù mr zuckerberg says ‚Äúhere we just value balance a lot more it takes work to build those relationships but if it does work you end up with a much better system‚Äùmr zuckerberg met ms sandberg at a christmas party in  and they immediately took a liking to each other what followed was an intense sixweek business courtship during which the two dined together multiple times a week because both of them are silicon valley celebrities they typically ate at ms sandberg‚Äôs house so they could keep their talks confidential‚Äúwe were very methodical and thoughtful about the relationship‚Äù says ms sandbergfor his part mr zuckerberg ever the tech geek describes their interactions as ‚Äúhighbandwidth‚Äù‚Äúwe can talk for  seconds and have more meaning be exchanged than in a lot of meetings that i have for an hour‚Äù he says ms sandberg might give him a quick update on say the development of facebook‚Äôs offices in ireland or india‚Äúi make sure that i understand the basic things that we are doing‚Äù says mr zuckerberg but he adds he trusts that anything ms sandberg handles will run smoothly ‚Äúthe dynamic on the management team‚Äù he says ‚Äúhas improved a huge amount since she joined‚Äù photo sheryl sandberg second from left and mark zuckerberg right in sun valley idaho in july they met with george bodenheimer left of espn and abc sports and robert a iger of disney credit mario anzuonireuters outside the company ms sandberg spends much of her time with advertisers last week for example she crisscrossed manhattan where she gave a keynote speech at an advertising week conference and met in private with various large advertisers advertisement continue reading the main story ms sandberg also oversees the seemingly arcane operational details that can help a company run smoothly ‚Äî especially a company that is growing rapidlyshe recently sat down with pedram keyani an engineer whose team builds the tools that handle complaints and requests from facebook‚Äôs users mr keyani said ms sandberg met with his small group to understand the challenges it faced and later reorganized it to run more smoothly‚Äúshe operates at every level‚Äù mr keyani says ‚Äúshe‚Äôs good at strategy and dives deep and understands how teams work together‚Äùthe embrace of ms sandberg by mr zuckerberg and facebook‚Äôs something rankandfile was not preordained when she was hired a frathouse atmosphere permeated the company according to many early employees and technology blogs speculated that she had been brought in to clean up the placeto this day ms sandberg looks a bit out of place at facebook she sits in a cluster of desks that includes mr zuckerberg‚Äôs as well as those of other engineering and product executives their penchant for jeans tshirts and hoodies is in sharp contrast to her taste for elegant clothing her own staff which handles most of facebook‚Äôs business functions works in another building a few blocks awayher efforts to win over the facebook troops began on her first day she went desk to desk to introduce herself cracking jokes and asking questions it had the desired effect‚Äúshe‚Äôs legit‚Äù says christopher cox a confidant of mr zuckerberg and the company‚Äôs vice president for product ‚Äúshe‚Äôs not like a robot mba the people who get rejected here are the people who come here and say all these mba words like ‚Äòsynergy‚Äô¬†‚Äù advertisement continue reading the main story ms sandberg earned a reputation for mentoring many younger employees ‚Äî especially women encouraging many of them not to shy away from important roles simply because they were planning to start families ms sandberg can speak to that topic from experience she is married to dave goldberg the chief executive of surveymonkey a maker of software for online surveys and the couple have two young childrenwhenever anyone on her side of the company is promoted she sends a congratulatory notepeople who have known ms sandberg a long time say they are not surprised by her success as a harvard undergraduate she sat near the back of an economics class taught by mr summers he says he didn‚Äôt pay much attention to her until she turned in the best midterm examination in her class ‚Äî and then the best finalmr summers became her thesis adviser and later hired her to work with him at the world bank and at the treasury department although she was still in her s she played pivotal roles like helping ramp up aid efforts to africa by opening treasury‚Äôs door to bono of u‚Äúi had never heard of him and said to sheryl that i only meet with people who have a first name and last name‚Äù mr summers recalls at ms sandberg‚Äôs urging he finally agreed debt relief in africa ‚Äúwouldn‚Äôt have happened if she hadn‚Äôt insisted i meet bono and persevered on this issue‚Äù says mr summersms sandberg‚Äôs connection with mr zuckerberg runs especially deep the two often socialize and mr zuckerberg who was captain of his high school fencing team has taught ms sandberg‚Äôs yearold son a few fencing moveswhen mr zuckerberg and priscilla chan his longtime girlfriend started thinking about philanthropy they turned to ms sandberg she immediately tapped her vast network of contacts and organized meetings with the likes of mayor michael r bloomberg of new york and michelle a rhee the schools chief in washington dcms sandberg ‚Äúhelped me navigate the politics of it and to figure out where i could have the most leverage‚Äù mr zuckerberg says ‚Äúthat she was the person that priscilla and i turned to is a strong symbol of our relationship‚Äù continue reading the main story we‚Äôre interested in your feedback on this page tell us what you think related coverage the media equation film version of zuckerberg divides the generations oct   zuckerberg‚Äôs legal options are slender oct   how a silicon valley investor views a postfacebook world oct   related coverage the media equation film version of zuckerberg divides the generations oct   zuckerberg‚Äôs legal options are slender oct   how a silicon valley investor views a postfacebook world oct   whats next loading go to home page ¬ª site index the new york times sheryl sandberg  wikipedia sheryl sandberg from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search sheryl sandberg sandberg at facebook london april  born sheryl kara sandberg  august   age¬† washington dc us residence menlo park california us alma¬†mater harvard university ba mba occupation coo of facebook years¬†active ‚Äìpresent salary us million  net¬†worth us billion july  political party democratic board member¬†of facebook the walt disney company women for women international center for global development vday surveymonkey spouses brian kraff m¬† div¬† dave goldberg m¬† d¬† children  with goldberg sheryl kara sandberg Ààs√¶ndb…ôr…° born august   is an american technology executive activist and author she is the chief operating officer coo of facebook and founder of leaninorg also known as the lean in foundation in june  she was elected to the board of directors by the existing board members becoming the first woman to serve on facebooks board before she joined facebook as its coo sandberg was vice president of global online sales and operations at google and was involved in launching googles philanthropic arm googleorg before google sandberg served as chief of staff for united states secretary of the treasury lawrence summers in  she was named in the time  an annual list of the  most influential people in the world according to time magazine as of june update sandberg is reported to be worth over us billion due to her stock holdings in facebook and other companies contents  early life and education  career  early career  facebook  boards  other work and ventures  lean in  ban bossy  sheryl sandberg  dave goldberg family foundation  personal life  honors  bibliography  references  external links early life and educationedit sandberg was born in  in washington dc to a jewish family the daughter of adele n√©e einhorn and joel sandberg and the oldest of three children her father is an ophthalmologist and her mother was a college teacher of french language adele taught english as a second language and founded ear peacesave your hearing a nonprofit that teaches teens how to prevent hearing loss she dropped out of a phd program when she was pregnant with sheryl and concentrated on raising her children sheryls maternal grandmother rosalind einhorn grew up in a poor family in a crowded apartment in new york city finished high school in spite of being pulled out during the great depression went on to community college graduated from uc berkeley and later saved her family business from financial ruin sandbergs family was active in helping soviet jews make aliyah to israel during the refusenik era and attended rallies during the weekends in  adele and joel were detained and interrogated in kishinev and later expelled from the ussr sheryl and her siblings had soviet bar and bat mitzvah twins who were called to the torah during their ceremonies as they could not have their own in the soviet union sheryls was a penpal named kira volvovskaya her family moved to north miami beach florida when she was  years old she attended north miami beach high school where she was always at the top of her class and graduated ninth in her class with a  grade point average she was sophomore class president became a member of the national honor society and was on the senior class executive board sandberg taught aerobics in the s while in high school in  sandberg enrolled at harvard college she graduated in  summa cum laude phi beta kappa with a bachelors degree in economics and was awarded the john h williams prize for the top graduating student in economics while at harvard she cofounded an organization called women in economics and government she met thenprofessor larry summers who became her mentor and thesis adviser summers recruited her to be his research assistant at the world bank where she worked for approximately one year on health projects in india dealing with leprosy aids and blindness in  she enrolled at harvard business school and in  she earned her mba with highest distinction in her first year of business school she earned a fellowship careeredit early careeredit after graduating from business school in the spring of  sandberg worked as a management consultant for mckinsey  company for approximately one year  from  to  she again worked for larry summers who was then serving as the united states secretary of the treasury under president bill clinton sandberg assisted in the treasurys work on forgiving debt in the developing world during the asian financial crisis when the republicans gained the us presidency in november  sandberg left her job she then moved to silicon valley in  and joined google inc serving as its vice president of global online sales and operations from november  to march  she was responsible for online sales of googles advertising and publishing products as well as for sales operations of googles consumer products and google book search facebookedit in late  mark zuckerberg cofounder and chief executive of facebook met sandberg at a christmas party held by dan rosensweig zuckerberg had no formal search for a coo but thought of sandberg as a perfect fit for this role in march  facebook announced hiring sandberg away from google for the role of coo after joining the company sandberg quickly began trying to figure out how to make facebook profitable before she joined the company was primarily interested in building a really cool site profits they assumed would follow by late spring facebooks leadership had agreed to rely on advertising with the ads discreetly presented by  facebook became profitable according to facebook she oversees the firms business operations including sales marketing business development human resources public policy and communications in  she became the eighth member and the first woman of facebooks board of directors in april  it was reported that sandberg had sold over half of her shares in facebook since the company went public at the time of facebooks ipo she held approximately  million shares in the company after several rounds of sales she is left with around  million shares a  stake in the company worth about  billion boardsedit in  sandberg was named to the board of the walt disney company she also serves on the boards of women for women international the center for global development and vday she was previously a board member of starbucks with a  annual salary brookings institution and ad council other work and venturesedit in  sandberg wrote an article for the huffington post in support of her mentor larry summers who was under fire for his comments about women she was a keynote speaker at the jewish community federations business leadership council in  in december  she gave a ted speech titled why we have too few women leaders in may  she gave the commencement address at the barnard college graduation ceremony she spoke as the keynote speaker at the class day ceremony at the harvard business school in may  in april  she was the keynote speaker for colgate universitys second annual entrepreneur weekend in  she signed an open letter which the one campaign had been collecting signatures for the letter was addressed to angela merkel and nkosazana dlaminizuma urging them to focus on women as they serve as the head of the g in germany and the au in south africa respectively which will start to set the priorities in development funding before a main un summit in september  that will establish new development goals for the generation lean inedit sandberg released her first book lean in women work and the will to lead coauthored by nell scovell and published by knopf on march   it is about business leadership and development issues with the lack of women in government and business leadership positions and feminism as of the fall of  the book sold more than one million copies and was on top of the bestseller lists since its launch lean in is a book for professional women to help them achieve their career goals and for men who want to contribute to a more equitable society the book argues that barriers are still preventing women from taking leadership roles in the workplace barriers such as discrimination blatant and subtle sexism and sexual harassment sandberg claims there are also barriers that women create for themselves through internalizing systematic discrimination and societal gender roles sandberg argues that in order for change to happen women need to break down these societal and personal barriers by striving for and achieving leadership roles the ultimate goal is to encourage women to lean in to positions of leadership because she believes that by having more female voices in positions of power there will be more equitable opportunities created for everyone ‚Äú a truly equal world would be one where women ran half our countries and companies and men ran half our homes ‚Äù criticism of the book include claims that sandberg is too elitist and another that she is tonedeaf to the struggles faced by the average woman in the workplace sandberg addresses both of these issues in the introduction of her book stating that she is acutely aware that the vast majority of women are struggling to make ends meet and take care of their families and that her intention was to offer advice that would have been useful long before i had heard of google or facebook ban bossyedit main article ban bossy in march  sandberg and lean in sponsored the controversial ban bossy campaign a television and social media censorship advocacy campaign designed to ban the word bossy from general use due to its perceived harmful effect on young girls several video spots with notable spokespersons including beyonc√© jennifer garner and condoleezza rice among others were produced along with a web site providing school training material leadership tips and an online pledge form to which visitors can promise not to use the word sheryl sandberg  dave goldberg family foundationedit in november  sandberg renamed her lean in foundation to the sheryl sandberg  dave goldberg family foundation this new foundation will serve as an umbrella for leaninorg and a new organization around her book option b sandberg also transferred roughly  in facebook stock to fund the foundation and other charitable endeavors personal lifeedit sandberg first married at age  and divorced a year later in  she married dave goldberg then an executive with yahoo and later ceo of surveymonkey the couple has a son and a daughter sandberg and goldberg frequently discussed being in a shared earningshared parenting marriage sandberg also raised the issue of single parenting conflicting strongly with professional and economic development in america on may   dave goldberg died unexpectedly and his death was originally reported as resulting from sustaining a head trauma falling from a treadmill while the couple was vacationing in mexico sandberg has subsequently said that her husbands cause of death was due to an arrhythmia and not due to falling from a treadmill sandberg lives in menlo park california honorsedit external video sheryl sandberg why we have too few women leaders ted barnard college commencement speech barnard college sheryl sandberg has been ranked one of the  most powerful women in business by fortune magazine in  she was ranked  and was the youngest woman on the list in  she was ranked  in  she was ranked  in  she was ranked  in  she was ranked  in  she was ranked  on the list of  women to watch by the wall street journal she was ranked  on that list in  she was ranked  on that list in  sandberg was named one of the  most influential people on the web by business week in  she has been listed as one of the worlds  most powerful women by forbes in  sandberg was listed as ninth just behind michelle obama in  newsweek and the daily beast released their first digital power index a list of the  most significant people in the digital world that year plus  additional lifetime achievement winners and she was ranked  in the evangelists category in  she was named in time  an annual list of the  most influential people in the world assembled by time lean in was shortlisted for the financial times and goldman sachs business book of the year award  in  she was ranked  on the worlds  most influential jews conducted by the jerusalem post sandberg delivered the commencement address at the graduation of university of california berkeleys class of  it was the first time she spoke publicly about her husbands death and stressed the importance of resilience sandberg was given the honor to deliver the commencement address at the graduation of virginia techs class of  bibliographyedit lean in women work and the will to lead knopf  isbn  written with adam grant option b facing adversity building resilience and finding joy knopf  isbn  referencesedit  a b carlyle erin october   facebook coo sheryl sandberg sells atherton home for  million forbescom retrieved april  ¬†  compensation information for sheryl k sandberg  coo of facebook inc salarycom retrieved april  ¬†  sheryl sandberg forbescom january   retrieved april  ¬†  a b c weddingscelebrations sheryl sandberg david goldberg the new york times april   p¬†style retrieved july  ¬†  eldon eric june   sheryl sandberg facebook‚Äôs longtime coo becomes first woman on its board of directors techcrunch retrieved october  ¬†  a b kent muhtar april   sheryl sandberg  the  most influential people time retrieved april  ¬†  de jong david january   sheryl sandberg becomes one of youngest us billionaires bloomberg retrieved january  ¬†  httpswwwinsidermolecominsidersandbergsheryl sandberg sheryl insider trading  a b c d e f g h i auletta ken july   a woman‚Äôs place the new yorker retrieved july  ¬†  benjamin a einhorn  death notice  classified miami herald october   ‚Äì via newsbank¬†  a b c d e dorschner john february   sheryl sandberg from north miami beach high to facebook‚Äôs no  the miami herald archived from the original on october   retrieved october  ¬†  samakow jessica may   adele sandberg sheryl sandbergs mom inspired daughter to l