ars‚Äî‚Äúa long time for anyone to be anywhere‚Äù she says but even though her name is frequently associated with highlevel roles such as walt disney co ceo or california senator she says she‚Äôs not going anywhere her argument is as always deployed with data and a handy vignette research shows that after experiencing a death it‚Äôs common for people to want to do something meaningful with their lives she says she thinks her work at facebook is more meaningful than everand in a sense the company is a kind of wealthy nationstate unto itself‚Äîone that might grant her more influence than she would have as a politician alongside encouraging warm open conversation among employees she and zuckerberg have implemented longer bereavement plans and more flex time for coping with life tragedies policies which if they spread to other companies would offer a tangible payoff for all this jobmandated vulnerability ‚Äúi work on something i really believe in with my best friend i think i‚Äôm doing this‚Äù she says of her intention to stay put ‚Äúi don‚Äôt know how many times to say it‚Äù ¬†corrects spelling of¬†deutch‚Äôs name in the th paragraph¬† sheryl sandberg  technology  the guardian close skip to main content tech us world environment us politics business science money obituaries more sign in comment activity edit profile email preferences change password sign out become a supporter subscribe search jobs us edition switch to the uk edition switch to the australia edition switch to the international edition the guardian  back to home browse all sections close sheryl sandberg may  sheryl sandberg is right the way america treats mothers has to change arwa mahdawi not only is childcare more than rent it often costs more than college it‚Äôs time to stop talking about ‚Äòfamily values‚Äô and start putting them into practice published  may  sheryl sandberg is right the way america treats mothers has to change april  notebook how donald trump was silenced emma brockes debating vacci